<div class="breadcrumb"><a href="">Home</a> &raquo; <a href="forum">forums</a> &raquo; <a href="forum/1">LtU Forum</a></div><h2>Anyone remember Russell (the language, that is)?</h2>
<!-- begin content -->
<div class="node">
 <div class="content">
<p >Russell was a functional language developed some 25 years ago to explore the idea of data types as full first-class objects.  I'm a total amateur when it comes to programming languages, but I remember thinking at the time that it was pretty cool.  A cursory search of Lambda and the web didn't turn up much.</p>
<p >The main reference looks to be:<br >
"Data Types are Values"<br >
TOPLAS, vol. 7, #3 (July 1985)</p> </div>
 <div class="links">By <a href="user/1843" title="View user profile.">beev</a> at 04/18/2005 - 19:02 | <a href="taxonomy/term/1">LtU Forum</a> | <a href="node/837" title="The Language Machine - a toolkit for language and grammar">previous forum topic</a> | <a href="node/1144" title="Interesting Logo Site: Elica">next forum topic</a> | <a href="http://www.technorati.com/search/lambda-the-ultimate.org/node/648" title="Technorati search of other blogs commenting on this post.">other blogs</a> | 1852 reads</div>
</div>
