 <h3 class="title"><a href="node/648#comment-12353" class="active">Russell - that&#039;s my language!</a></h3>
 <div class="content"><p >Scary and funny. This evening, I'm finishing writing tomorrow's lecture in computer science. I've been teaching postgradutes for the last 10 years, and tomorrow is the first time they let me near 1st years ;-).<br >
I was just doing up a few slides of background, trying to make them understand the larger frame of computer science, so I Googled Russell Programming Language, that IMHO was created by me in the early 80s. Lo and B-hold, I found these pages! I've downloaded the stuff from the xerox server and will carefully look if there's any resemblance...<br >
I named MY language after Bertrand Russell, after reading Primcipia Mathematica and having interesting discussions on various CompuServe fourms about set theory...</p></div>
